#Vile Consumption (#1085): all creatures get "at your upkeep, sacrifice this
#unless you pay 1 life". Decline at my T3 upkeep -> bears sacrificed (or pay:
#life 19). On master NEITHER happens.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{1}{U}{B}
hand:vile consumption
inplay:grizzly bears
library:darksteel citadel,millstone
[PLAYER2]
library:darksteel citadel,millstone
[DO]
vile consumption
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto end
goto firstmain
goto end
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
choice 1
goto upkeep
goto upkeep
[ASSERT]
UPKEEP
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:grizzly bears
inplay:vile consumption
library:darksteel citadel,millstone
[PLAYER2]
hand:*
library:darksteel citadel
[END]
#PARKED: 3rd granted-upcost witness (thirst, vapor_snare_upcost cousins). The
#lord(creature) transforms((,newability[upcost[{L:1}] sacrifice])) grant never
#registers its AUpkeep - no prompt, no sacrifice, the enchantment is a no-op.
#The complaint ("needs a prompt for the payment or sacrifice") is literal.
#Engine fuel: wire AUpkeep registration for granted/teach-granted abilities.
